Police officers in Kilungu sub-county, Makueni County, are holding a middle-aged woman in connection with the murder of her husband. The deceased is said to have gone missing about two weeks ago before the skull of his head and bone were later discovered  in their garden a few meters from their home at Thoma village in Kola area. County Police Commander Joseph Ole Napeiyan, speaking to the press on Sunday, said the deceased’s clothes were also recovered, adding that the other remains of his body are yet to be found. Napeiyan further stated that drops of blood were found on a machete and a shovel that were recovered on scene, suggesting that he could have been killed at home. The machete and shovel were confiscated and will be used as evidence in the case, with the deceased’s wife being held in lawful custody. Also Read: Video Of The Day: KEMRI scientists examine safety of anti-malarial drugs in first trimester of pregnancy